

<div class="row">
  <div class="col-sm-12">
    <%= image_tag("https://s3.amazonaws.com/citkents/kk-logo-2.png") %>
    <div class="col-sm-6">
      <div id="map"  class="child" style="margin-top: 10px;"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6 pull-right getaway">
      <div class="well comparison kent-well animated bounceInRight">
        <h3><%= kents.name %></h3>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-sm-6 col-xs-6"><h4>Scores:</h4></div>
          <div class="col-sm-6 col-xs-6 pull-right">
            <h4 class="kentstotal pull-right">Average: <%= '%.2f' % kents.total_average %></h4>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="text-center">Price</p>
        <%= render partial: "/eateries/average_bar", locals: { property: kents.average_price } %>
        <p class="text-center">Portion</p>
        <%= render partial: "/eateries/average_bar", locals: { property: kents.average_portion } %>
        <p class="text-center">Taste</p>
        <%= render partial: "/eateries/average_bar", locals: { property: kents.average_taste } %>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6">
      <br>
      <p>How do the eateries you've visited compare to Kent's Kitchen? It is the opinion of the world renowned food connoisseur Andrew that Kent's has the best PPTâ„¢ ratio of any eatery in Vancouver. PPT stands for Price, Portion, and Taste - Kent's offers the best tasting food in the largest portion for the lowest price. Unless you think otherwise? Share your reviews of other eateries in comparison to Kent's.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="clearfix"></div>
    <div class="col-sm-6">
      <blockquote class="pull-right">
        <p>My life has gotten so much better ever since I put Kent's inside me.</p>
        <small><cite title="Josh">Josh</cite></small>
      </blockquote>
      <blockquote>
        <p>A revolutionary revolutionizing revolution of groundbreakingness.</p>
        <small><cite title="Chris">My Landlord Larry</cite></small>
      </blockquote>
      <blockquote>
        <p>Why would you set the bar so low??</p>
        <small><cite title="Tammam Kbeili">Tam </cite></small>
      </blockquote>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<script type="text/javascript">
  
  handler = Gmaps.build('Google');
  handler.buildMap({ provider: {}, internal: {id: 'map'}}, function(){
    markers = handler.addMarkers(<%= raw generate_map_json([kents]).to_json %>);
    handler.bounds.extendWith(markers);
    handler.fitMapToBounds();
    handler.getMap().setZoom(12);
  });

</script>